SIMPLE: currentness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Currentness
<hw>Cur"rent*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of
being current; currency; circulation; general reception.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Easiness of pronunciation; fluency.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When <qex>currentness</qex> [combineth] with staidness, how can
the language . . . sound other than most full of sweetness?</q>
<rj><qau>Camden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Curricle</ent>⟦br⟧
